0 0 0 fC
396 243 1269 (compare function in the working paper.  The text tends to talk) 1269 SB
396 299 1074 (of "function object", but it is nowhere specified that a) 1074 SB
396 355 1276 (compare function needs to be an object.  With most algorithms) 1276 SB
396 411 1278 (that take a compare function it seems to be reasonable to allow) 1278 SB
396 467 118 (functi) 118 SB
514 467 784 (on objects as well as function pointers.) 784 SB
396 579 1217 (On the other hand with the associative containers the intent) 1217 SB
396 635 1131 (seems to be a little bit different.  E.g. the constructors of) 1131 SB
396 691 1287 (those containers take a compare argument, which has a default) 1287 SB
396 747 1193 (value of Compare\(\), which is the default constructor of the) 1193 SB
396 803 1303 (Compare type provided as template parameter of the container.) 1303 SB
396 859 1201 (If a user wants to work with a function pointer instead of a) 1201 SB
396 915 1214 (function object he/she can do so. The only inconvenience is) 1214 SB
396 971 695 (that he/she cannot rely on the def) 695 SB
1091 971 427 (ault value and has to) 427 SB
396 1027 1203 (explicitly provide the compare parameter in all cases. \(This) 1203 SB
396 1083 1299 (would be true for function compare objects that have no default) 1299 SB
396 1139 411 (constructor as well.\)) 411 SB
396 1251 1170 (So, there seems to be no reason to assume that a compare) 1170 SB
396 1307 823 (function could not be a function pointer.) 823 SB
396 1419 1219 (But then, a library implementer has the latitude to offer two) 1219 SB
396 1475 1266 (constructors instead of one with a defaulted argument. In that) 1266 SB
396 1531 1328 (case the default constructor would make some assumption about) 1328 SB
396 1587 950 (the default value for the compare function, wh) 950 SB
1346 1587 255 (ich probably) 255 SB
396 1643 1351 (would be Compare\(\) again. Hence with such an implementation it) 1351 SB
396 1699 956 (would not be possible to use function pointers.) 956 SB
